Add the following to include/net/sock.h.

Near the top of the file, alongside the other includes:

	#include <net/net-delayacct.h>

Inside struct sock, near other accounting-related fields (for example
after `struct sk_filter __rcu *sk_filter;` or in the trailing
#ifdef-protected section), add:

	#ifdef CONFIG_NET_DELAYACCT
	struct net_delayacct		sk_net_delayacct;
	#endif

Rationale: keeping the field #ifdef-protected means a kernel compiled
without CONFIG_NET_DELAYACCT sees no ABI change and no memory growth.
The per-socket spinlock is independent of sk->sk_lock.slock to avoid
lock-ordering issues with the socket lock taken in the RX/TX paths.

The complete unified diff (apply with `git apply` or `patch -p1`
from the root of a Linux 6.6 source tree):

--- a/include/net/sock.h
+++ b/include/net/sock.h
@@ -XXX,XXX @@
 #include <net/tcp_states.h>
 #include <net/net_namespace.h>
+#include <net/net-delayacct.h>
 #include <net/net_namespace.h>
@@ -XXX,XXX @@ struct sock {
 	struct sk_filter __rcu	*sk_filter;
+#ifdef CONFIG_NET_DELAYACCT
+	struct net_delayacct	sk_net_delayacct;
+#endif
 	struct socket_wq __rcu	*sk_wq;

Note: the exact context lines may vary slightly between 6.6.x point
releases.  When applying, locate struct sk_filter in include/net/sock.h
and add the new field immediately after it.
